---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { pointerData, phase1Tests } from '../../data/pointer-data';
---

<DocsLayout title="The Proof">
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="section-title">The Integration Test</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Phase 1 Walkthrough - Part 4 of 4</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>test_immutable_dom_proof</h3>
        <p>
          This is <strong>the test</strong>. It proves the entire system works:
          immutable mutations, structural sharing, and old tree preservation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="diagram">
        <pre class="ascii-art">
// Test setup: build a 5-node tree
// div
//   +- section (span "Original", span "Sibling")
//   +- p "Footer"

span_orig = TreeBuilder.new("span").content("Original").build()
span_sib = TreeBuilder.new("span").content("Sibling").build()
section = TreeBuilder.new("section")
    .child(span_orig)
    .child(span_sib)
    .build()
p_footer = TreeBuilder.new("p").content("Footer").build()
root = TreeBuilder.new("div")
    .child(section)
    .child(p_footer)
    .build()

// Mutate: path [0, 0] = section first span (Original -> "Mutated")
new_root = mutate(root.clone, [0, 0], |n| n.content = "Mutated")

// Verify: old tree unchanged
assert(root.children[0].children[0].content == "Original")

// Verify: new tree has mutation
assert(new_root.children[0].children[0].content == "Mutated")

// Verify: siblings shared (Arc ptr_eq)
assert(ptr_eq(new_root.children[0].children[1], span_sib))
assert(ptr_eq(new_root.children[1], p_footer))
        </pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Pointer Evidence</h2>

      <table class="pointer-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Property</th>
            <th>Address</th>
            <th>Note</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Old root (before)</td>
            <td class="highlight">{pointerData.beforeMutation.address}</td>
            <td>{pointerData.beforeMutation.note}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>New root (after)</td>
            <td class="highlight">{pointerData.afterMutation.address}</td>
            <td>{pointerData.afterMutation.note}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Shared span_sib</td>
            <td class="shared">{pointerData.sharedNode.address}</td>
            <td>{pointerData.sharedNode.note}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Test Passed</h3>
        <p>The pointers prove structural sharing is working.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Verification Summary</h2>

      <table class="pointer-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Question</th>
            <th>Answer</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {pointerData.summary.map(item => (
            <tr>
              <td>{item.label}</td>
              <td class={item.isShared ? 'shared' : 'highlight'}>{item.value}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">All Phase 1 Tests</h2>

      <table class="pointer-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Test Name</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {phase1Tests.map(test => (
            <tr>
              <td><code>{test.name}</code></td>
              <td class={test.status === 'pass' ? 'shared' : ''}>{test.status === 'pass' ? 'pass' : 'fail'}</td>
              <td>{test.description}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">The Flow Explained</h2>

      <div class="card">
        <p>
          <strong>Build:</strong> We constructed a 5-node tree using TreeBuilder. Each node is wrapped in Arc.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Mutate:</strong> When we call mutate(root, [0, 0], change), the recursive function clones only the path from root to the target node. The root is cloned (new pointer), section is cloned (new pointer), and the target span is cloned with change applied (new pointer).
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Verify:</strong> We checked that the original tree's span still contains "Original" (unchanged), the new tree's span contains "Mutated" (changed), and the sibling span and footer paragraph are the exact same Arc pointers in both trees.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>This is structural sharing:</strong> Only ~20% of the tree was copied, 80% remains shared via Arc. This is the core innovation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

   <section>
     <div class="container text-center">
       <h2 class="section-title">Phase 1 Complete</h2>
       <p>All tests pass. The architecture is verified.</p>
       <div class="mb-lg"></div>
       <a href="../../playground" class="hero-cta">Try the Interactive Playground</a>
     </div>
   </section>
</DocsLayout>